                <head>Thrilling Eloquence</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Reprint of speech by Rep. Boder of Virginia, recalling Virginia volunteers
                    in the Revolutionary War who fought in Massachusetts, and pointing out that they
                    had been repaid with John Brown's raid.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>06</column>
                <head>Sentence of Death</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Transcript of sentencing remarks of judge in trial of Aaron Stevens and
                    Albert Hazelett, two members of John Brown's raiding party, who were given death
                    sentences.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
