            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head>Reaping Their Reward</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Claims that New England shoemakers are suffering from the lack of business
                    because of boycotts by the South.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>03</column>
                <head>For the Valley Spirit</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Respectfully, Oglethorpe</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Letter from Charlestown, Virginia, talking about the condemned men of
                    Brown's raid, and relating several anecdotes attributed to Brown himself. His
                    followers are described as intelligent but fanatical men.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>06</column>
                <head>Sectionalism in Congress</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Compares chairmanships of committees in Congress to demonstrate that
                    Republican claims of Southern domination of Congress are unfounded.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
        </page>
